    <section id="Atlantic Avenue United Church">
        <h3>Atlantic Avenue United Church</h3>
        <p>
            In 1926, the vision of a permanent structure was introduced.  This was a giant undertaking for the
            congregation. Funds had to be raised and plans for a new church studied.  It was decided to go ahead with
            the new building and in the fall of 1927, another milestone in our history was the laying of the cornerstone
            for the present structure.  On December 7, 1927, the church was completed and on December 11, 1927, the
            opening service and dedication was held in the new building as it stands today.  We were now Atlantic Avenue
            United Church.  Our first minister was Rev. Robert Frayne who served until 1935.
        </p>
