    <section id="The_Manse">
        <h3>The Manse</h3>
        <p>
            In 1950, a manse was built at 721 Atlantic Avenue, next door to the church.  During the 1970's, this
            building ceased to be used as a manse and became a Christian Education facility.  It was sold in 2000.
        </p>
    </section>
    <section id="Garden_City_United_Church">
        <h3>Garden City United Church</h3>
        <p>
            As homes were being built in the Garden City area, people there began planning for a church to serve them.
            In 1962, a portable building was moved from Windsor Park to a site at Airlies and Merriwood to be used as a
            church.  It was known as Garden City United Church.  Unfortunately, due to a lack of finances and support,
            the final service was held on June 8, 1967.  The Garden City United Church congregation then amalgamated
            with the Atlantic Avenue United Church congregation and the new name of the church was Atlantic-Garden City
            United Church.
        </p>
    </section>
